  "prompt": "How often should one visit a dentist?",
  "response": "It is generally recommended to visit a dentist every six months for a routine check-up and cleaning. However, the frequency can vary depending on individual dental health needs. Some people with certain conditions or higher risk of dental issues may need to visit more often, while others with excellent oral health might get by with annual visits. It's best to follow the advice of your dentist, who can tailor recommendations based on your personal oral health.",
